owl:Ontology.terms:title: TODODom: Domain Module for Task-Oriented Dialogue management Ontology (TODO)

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between an Argument and the WorldElements that can be associated to it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: appliesToWorld

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between an Argument and a WorldElement that can be associated to it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: appliesToWorldElement

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between an Argument and a WorldElementGroup that can be associated to it.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: appliesToWorldElementGroup

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between a WorldElementGroup and a member of said group.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasGroupMember

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between a FrameHead/WorldElement and one of its corresponding Lexical Units.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasLexicalUnit

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes a relation between a TargetSystemReadableInformation element and its specific implementation in the target system (specification).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasSpecification

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between an Action/Argument/WorldElement and its corresponding TargetSystemReadableInfo.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasTargetSystemReadableInfo

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relationship between an element and its Trace.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasTrace

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment:
(In a guide robot, with guiding and information functionalities; the TSRI of the destinations are coordinates and the TSRI of the elements to obtain information about are IDs)
Destination_guideRobot hasTSRI ?x . ?x hasType coordinate .
PieceInformation_guideRobot has TSRI ?y . ?y hasType ID .
Establishes a relation between an Action/Argument/WorldElement TSRI and its TSRI type.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasType

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between an ArgumentTrace and its corresponding value (WorldElement).
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: hasValue

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between a WorldElement and the Argument(s) that it can be associated to.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isApplicableToArgument

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between a Lexical Unit and its corresponding FrameHead/WorldElement.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isLexicalUnitOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between a WorldElement and a WorldElementGroup, which is a member of.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isMemberOfGroup

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relation between a TargetSystemReadableInfon and the Action/Argument/WorldElement it corresponds to.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isTargetSystemReadableInfoOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment: Establishes the relationship between a Trace and the element it refers to.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isTraceOf

owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:comment:
(In a guide robot, with guiding and information functionalities; the TSRI of the destinations are coordinates and the TSRI of the elements to obtain information about are IDs)
Destination_guideRobot hasTSRI ?x . coordinate isTypeOf ?x .
PieceInformation_guideRobot has TSRI ?y . ID isTypeOf ?y .
Establishes a relation between a TSRI type and the Action/Argument/WorldElement TSRI with said TSRI type.
owl:ObjectProperty.rdfs:label: isTypeOf

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Sets specific implementation information for a Service.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: implementation

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Sets the order in which each argument needs to be output to the target system.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: order

owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:comment: Sets the value of a TSRI to be input to the target system.
owl:DatatypeProperty.rdfs:label: val

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class Action.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ActionTSRI

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Element that leaves a record of an Action obtained throughout the dialogue process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ActionTrace
ActionType
owl:Class.skos:example: Action: obtain_information -> it is directed towards API REST service The TSRI for obtain_information has an ActionType "service".
Establishes the TSRI type of an Action.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class Argument.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ArgumentTSRI

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Element that leaves a record of an Argument obtained throughout the dialogue process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ArgumentTrace

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Element that covers the information to execute an Action that is executable through a command (vs. as a Service).
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Command

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class Action that require information in a Command format.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: CommandTSRI

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Element that leaves a record of a Frame obtained throughout the dialogue process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: FrameTrace

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Establishes the TSRI type of a given Action/Parameter.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: InfoType

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Element that leaves a record of an Intent obtained throughout the dialogue process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: IntentTrace

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Word(s) that cover the different variants of a FrameHead or a WorldElement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: LexicalUnit
owl:Class.skos:example: FrameHead: go LexUnits (in Spanish): ir.V, desplazarse.V

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Establishes the type of parameter of a TSRI.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ParameterType
owl:Class.skos:example:
"baño" hasTSRI "coords_baño" "baño" hasTSRI "ID_baño"
"coords_baño" is of ParameterType "coordinate" "ID_baño" is of ParameterType "ID"

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class Action that point to Services.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: ServiceTSRI

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Element that leaves a record of a Skill obtained throughout the dialogue process.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: SkillTrace

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Information that is sent to the system to perform an execution or as argument for an execution, in a format that is understandable to the target system.

Plain language for whole action: Pick plastic container
SystemReadableInfo for "pick": robAction.Pick SystemReadableInfo for "plastic container": containerID:235
SystemReadableInfo for whole action: robAction.Pick(containerID:235)
owl:Class.rdfs:label: TargetSystemReadableInformation

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Agrupation of WorldElements of similar characteristics.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: WorldElementGroup

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Target System Readable Information corresponding to elements of the class WorldElement.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: WorldElementTSRI
